[Course_Description]
Get a first look at the new and enhanced features available in Scratch 3.0, the block-based (drag-and-drop) visual programming language. Hear about the differences between versions, specifically 2.0 and 3.0. Find out about changes to the interface and where to locate new extensions. Discover the new blocks that have been added. Learn how to use the enhancements found in the image editor and the sound editor. Find out how to create custom blocks. Watch how to use Scratch on a mobile device. Explore new enhancements for video, text, and robots. Deepa Muralidhar covers all these items, and more, in this course.